  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Marine Assistant",
  "description": "<p>Candidates are expected to:-</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform lookout duties on the craft:</li>\n  <li>Handle craft's mooring ropes during berthing and unberthing;</li>\n  <li>Assist passengers in their safe embarkation and disembarkation;</li>\n  <li>Maintain cleanliness of the deck, engine room and wheelhours of the craft; and</li>\n  <li>Perform any other duties as assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>*Candidates can look forward to professional skills and career development in PSA Marine as they embark on Port Limit Steersman / Engine Driver 3 courses to upgrade and deepen their knowledge, skills and abilities.</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>The ideal candidate should preferably:-</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Possess at least GCE N/O Levels, Nitec/Higher Nitec qualifications; and</li>\n  <li>Be willing to perform shift work.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>*Monthly salary as advertised is basic salary. Monthly gross salary includes night shift and special transport allowance, productivity incentive and meal allowances where applicable.</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Successful candidates will be deployed to either West Coast or Brani.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>*New hires may be eligible for a sign-on bonus of up to S$3,000. Terms and conditions apply.</strong></p>",
